al equilibrium and is bound with a $\\sim$80%\nprobability. We also find a velocity gradient in the stellar surface population\nof $\\sim$1.0 km s$^{-1}$pc$^{-1}$ in the northwest/southeast direction, which\nis consistent with that found for the pre-stellar dense cores, and we discuss\nthe possibility of sequential and triggered star formation in L1688.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 20 Jan 2016 09:21:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-03-30"}
